Regarding Gamma World:   TSR's Gamma World was under-developed SciFi garbage.  Game Designer's Workshop's Traveller universe was far superior in those days.  <br>
<br>
GDW's Traveller had ZERO competition in the area of Sci Fi RPGs in that time period.  Traveller was then the undisputed best selling and most talked about SciFi RPG ---- they had their act together.  The universe of the Third Imperium (the official game world of Traveller)  was the most sophisticated and most developed literature and RPG universe in that time.  It rivaled the World of Greyhawk or Forgotten Realms as far as history and depth.  <br>
<br>
By the time of the late 1980s and early 1990s, GURPs as well as the Star Trek and Star Wars role playing games were starting to take the Sci Fi RPG genre by storm.... and roughly at the same time Traveller was on its deathbed.<br>
<br>
There are still over 2 dozen nostalgic websites/fansites devoted to the Traveller universe today.  I dont think you can say the same thing about Gamma World or Boot Hill. <br>
<br>
And if not playing D&amp;D or Traveller back in those days.... then me and my friends/brothers were playing either Car Wars the original edition, or Illuminati the card game (also the plastic bag original first edition) <br>
<br>
For me there was also those Avalon Hill wargames.... <br>
<br>
I never did get into the Cyberpunk-ish RPG games.  Tho we tried out some of the silly silly beer and pretzels games like the Milton Bradley plastic army men games ---- Fortress America, Shogun, Axis and Allies.  And of course Risk and Diplomacy. <br>
<br>
<br>
