<br>
Facts? Please do explain these facts. If you mean his use of imagery from places he has visited or real life events at that time, then yes I agree with you, he used them very effectivly.<br>
<br>
If, however, you are refering to anything occult, such as the Necronomicon being an actual tome, then you are mistaken. That book was entirly created by Lovecraft himself, and the Mythos he uses was also created by him and, over time, other writers (August Derleth was the one who coined the term &quot;Cthulhu Mythos&quot;, HPL never used it). <br>
I've known people who believe this book to be real, mistaking the Simon &quot;Necronomicon&quot; for such. That book is hoax, mixing Crowley's idea with Sumerian mythos with Cthulhu mythos added for flavor. <br>
<br>
Just want to know which facts you mean <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
