<br>
I'm still waiting for a movie project that does his work justice.  There have been some really bad attempts at bringing Lovecraftian materials to the screen and you'll find his influences in a number of movies...but I wanna see the real deal.  His material would also make a great television series - turn of the century explorers and scientists battling the unseen forces of the occult to bring Cthulhu back!<br>
<br>
This reminds me.  There was this first person computer game that came out, back when Wolfenstein 3D was all the rage, that borrowed HEAVILY from the Cthulhu mythos.  I think the game was called &quot;The Legacy&quot; or something like that and it was very innovative for its time, although it didn't really take off.  As I recall, you could roll up a customized investigator and allocate points in the areas of strength, agility and psychic powers.  As you advanced you could increase your status in those areas and gain new powers.  It was very cool and I've been looking for a copy of it over the last while, but to no avail.  If anyone recalls the game, please lemme know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=banegrivm>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 563<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/30/03 11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_star.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: More trivia...</span><hr size=1> Yep, and the Traveller that got reprinted wasn't the goody Mega Traveller or Traveller the New Era...it was the original Traveller <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As to Cthulu mythos, Its been said that it can be traced all the way back to ancient Babylon. There is a deity there who encompases all the same things that were spoken of in the Cthulu Mythos and if I remember correctly they include the description. Scholars have said they believe that may be the source and origin of the Cthulu mythos.<br>
<br>
Then there is the &quot;Mad Arab&quot; who was said to have preached the edicts of Cthulu for the first time, as Cthulu. The full spelling of his name escapes me however.  <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>
