As for a Lovecraft movie, you should check out &quot;Dagon&quot;, it's kind of a mixture of Shadow over Innsmouth and Dagon, but is by far one of the better Lovecraft inspired movies I've seen yet, along with &quot;In the Mouth of Madness&quot;, not based of a story, but heavily Lovecraft influenced.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As to Cthulu mythos, Its been said that it can be traced all the way back to ancient Babylon. There is a deity there who encompases all the same things that were spoken of in the Cthulu Mythos and if I remember correctly they include the description. Scholars have said they believe that may be the source and origin of the Cthulu mythos.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wrong! Cthulhu Mythos was entirely invented by Lovecraft, and he never once used any Babylonian references (many other writers also used Cthulhu mythos in their stories, so maybe one of them used said references I'd have to check.) <br>
<br>
The Mad Arab you refer to is named Abdul Alhazred, which was a name that Lovecraft invented after reading The Arabian Nights when he was 5 yrs old. That's what he called himself when playing.<br>
<br>
Here's a link that sounds alot like where some of your information comes from <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.digital-brilliance.com/necron/necron.htm#What" target="top">Necronomicon Anti-FAQ</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Now here's a link that shows the inaccuracies of the last link, and even shows that the author of the former meant what he wrote in jest<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/SoHo/9879/necfaq.htm" target="top">Necronomicon Anti-FAQ WITF commentary</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Please do look through the site at that last link, it is very informative pertaining to all things Lovecraft and the Necronomicon. Here is another site dedicated to HPL and his writings <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hplovecraft.com/" target="top">The H.P. Lovecraft Archive</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
